                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su"
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "As a standard action, a skrell can make a single tentacle attack against an opponent they began their turn grappling, wrapping the appendage around its head. A successful attack deals 2d8+10 damage (instead of the tentacle\u2019s usual piercing damage) as the skrell assaults the target\u2019s mind. On a critical hit, the target also moves one step down the Intelligence poison track if it fails a DC 18 Will saving throw. This is a mind-affecting effect.",
                "name": "Mindsiphon",
